# EtherCAT Watchdog Recovery

Open this notebook with a Mix project runtime rooted at this repository.

This notebook checks the output watchdog behaviour of the running setup:
prime a few outputs high, stop domain cycling, wait for the output slave to
fall to `:safeop`, then restart cycling and confirm recovery to `:op`.

## Setup

<!-- livebook:{"attrs":"e30","chunks":null,"kind":"Elixir.KinoEtherCAT.SmartCells.Setup","livebook_object":"smart_cell"} -->

```elixir

```

## Helpers

```elixir
await_input = fn slave, signal, expected, timeout_ms ->
  deadline = System.monotonic_time(:millisecond) + timeout_ms

  Stream.repeatedly(fn -> EtherCAT.read_input(slave, signal) end)
  |> Enum.reduce_while(nil, fn value, _acc ->
    cond do
      value == expected ->
        {:halt, :ok}

      System.monotonic_time(:millisecond) >= deadline ->
        {:halt, {:error, {:timeout, slave, signal, expected, value}}}

      true ->
        Process.sleep(20)
        {:cont, nil}
    end
  end)
end

await_slave_state = fn slave, expected_state, timeout_ms ->
  deadline = System.monotonic_time(:millisecond) + timeout_ms

  Stream.repeatedly(fn -> EtherCAT.slave_info(slave) end)
  |> Enum.reduce_while(nil, fn
    {:ok, %{al_state: ^expected_state} = info}, _acc ->
      {:halt, {:ok, info}}

    {:ok, info}, _acc ->
      if System.monotonic_time(:millisecond) >= deadline do
        {:halt, {:error, {:timeout, slave, expected_state, info.al_state}}}
      else
        Process.sleep(20)
        {:cont, nil}
      end

    other, _acc ->
      {:halt, {:error, other}}
  end)
end
```

## Configuration

```elixir
domain_id = :main
pairs = [ch1: :ch1, ch2: :ch2]
settle_ms = 250
trip_timeout_ms = 2_000
recover_timeout_ms = 5_000
```

## Prime Outputs

```elixir
Enum.map(pairs, fn {output_signal, input_signal} ->
  :ok = EtherCAT.write_output(:outputs, output_signal, 1)

  %{
    output: output_signal,
    input: input_signal,
    high: await_input.(:inputs, input_signal, 1, settle_ms)
  }
end)
```

## Stop Cycling And Observe Safe State

```elixir
:ok = EtherCAT.Domain.stop_cycling(domain_id)

safeop = await_slave_state.(:outputs, :safeop, trip_timeout_ms)

loopback_low =
  Enum.map(pairs, fn {_output_signal, input_signal} ->
    %{input: input_signal, low: await_input.(:inputs, input_signal, 0, settle_ms)}
  end)

%{
  safeop: safeop,
  loopback_low: loopback_low
}
```

## Restart Cycling And Verify Recovery

```elixir
:ok = EtherCAT.Domain.start_cycling(domain_id)

recovery = await_slave_state.(:outputs, :op, recover_timeout_ms)

loopback_high =
  Enum.map(pairs, fn {output_signal, input_signal} ->
    :ok = EtherCAT.write_output(:outputs, output_signal, 1)

    %{output: output_signal, input: input_signal, high: await_input.(:inputs, input_signal, 1, settle_ms)}
  end)

%{
  recovery: recovery,
  loopback_high: loopback_high
}
```

## Tidy Up

```elixir
Enum.each(pairs, fn {output_signal, _input_signal} ->
  :ok = EtherCAT.write_output(:outputs, output_signal, 0)
end)

:ok = EtherCAT.Domain.start_cycling(domain_id)
:ok
```
